{#-
  Status — labelled status indicator with optional pulse.

  Compose Badge visual envelope (soft pill) + a leading colored dot. Used
  for live monitoring contexts (uptime, presence, queue size). The variant
  drives the live-region role per the OQ-mini Status resolution sealed
  S2.6 — mirrors Alert.md §"role auto-derives from variant" doctrine
  sealed in [ADR-0008]:

    variant ∈ {success, info, warning} → <output> (implicit role="status",
                                                    aria-live="polite",
                                                    aria-atomic="true")
    variant === 'danger'                → <div role="alert">  (assertive
                                                                auto-bump)

  Native `<output>` is preferred for polite variants — its implicit ARIA
  semantics avoid the SR double-announce trap when both implicit + explicit
  `aria-live` are present (per Sonner.md §3 "Why <output> and not <div
  role='status'>").

  Pulse animation (opt-in) is CSS-only :
    - 1500 ms loop = ~0.67 Hz, well under the 3 Hz epilepsy floor
      (per [13-a11y §15]).
    - Animates the dot's scale + a pseudo-element ring outside.
    - prefers-reduced-motion : skip animation, dot stays solid.

  Parameters:
    variant   (string, optional) success (default) | info | warning | danger
    label     (string, required) the visible status text (consumer-resolved)
    pulse     (bool,   optional) default false. true → animated dot for
                                  live-monitoring contexts.
    size      (string, optional) sm | md (default)
    className (string, optional)
-#}

{%- set variant   = variant   | default('success') -%}
{%- set label     = label     | default('') -%}
{%- set pulse     = pulse     | default(false) -%}
{%- set size      = size      | default('md') -%}
{%- set className = className | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-status'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _isDanger = variant == 'danger' -%}

{%- if _isDanger -%}
<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-variant="{{ variant }}"
  data-size="{{ size }}"
  {%- if pulse %} data-pulse="true"{% endif %}
  role="alert"
>
  <span class="theme-status__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="theme-status__label">{{ label }}</span>
</div>
{%- else -%}
<output
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-variant="{{ variant }}"
  data-size="{{ size }}"
  {%- if pulse %} data-pulse="true"{% endif %}
>
  <span class="theme-status__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="theme-status__label">{{ label }}</span>
</output>
{%- endif -%}
